        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- AI Ecosystem -->
    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2 class="faq-section-title">AI Ecosystem</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Which AI tools complement Claude Code?</summary>
          <p>Claude Code works best in an ecosystem: <strong>Perplexity</strong> for deep research with verified sources, <strong>Gemini</strong> for visual understanding (design &rarr; code), <strong>NotebookLM</strong> for document review and audio synthesis, <strong>v0/Bolt</strong> for rapid UI prototyping, <strong>Cursor/Copilot</strong> for inline autocomplete, and <strong>Wispr Flow</strong> for voice-to-text (4x faster than typing at 150 WPM). Chain them: Research (Perplexity) &rarr; Implement (Claude Code) &rarr; Deliver.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I use voice-to-text with Claude Code?</summary>
          <p>Tools like <strong>Wispr Flow</strong> or Superwhisper transcribe speech directly into the terminal at ~150 WPM (vs 40 WPM typing). This is particularly effective for writing detailed prompts and specifications. Setup is simple: install the app, select the terminal as input target, and dictate naturally.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can Claude Code work offline or with local models?</summary>
