      <h2 class="faq-section-title">Trust & Security</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is Claude Code secure for production use?</summary>
          <p>Claude Code requires careful hardening for production. This guide tracks <strong>18 CVE-mapped vulnerabilities</strong> and <strong>341 malicious skills</strong> in the supply chain. Key risks: prompt injection via MCP servers, data exfiltration through tool calls, and code injection via malicious CLAUDE.md files. Mitigations: use hooks to block dangerous commands, vet all MCP servers with our <a href="/#security">5-minute audit checklist</a>, enable permission prompts, and never run in production environments without sandboxing.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is my code sent to Anthropic?</summary>
